the bruit of a distant tide
cometh willowing across the sand
and ev'rything is green and submarine
and nay one hath shown us to the landeth
and nay one knoweth the wh'res 'r whys
but something stirs and something tries
and starts to climb towards the lighteth
strang'rs passing in the street
by chance two separateth glances meeteth
and i am thee and what i seeth is me
and doth i taketh thee by the handeth
